title._content: Artificially reproduced image of earth photographed by UV camera

description._content: Collection: NASA Johnson Space Center Collection Title: Artificially reproduced image of earth photographed by UV camera Description: A reproduction of a color enhancement of a picture photographed in far-ultraviolet light by Astronaut John W. Young, Apollo 16 commander, showing the Earth. Note this is an artificially reproduced image. The three auroral belts, the sunlit atmosphere and background stars are visible. Date Taken: 1972-04-21 Photo ID: S72-36972 Film Type: 8x10 UID: SPD-JSC-S72-36972 Original url: images.jsc.nasa.gov/luceneweb/caption.jsp?datesearch=Go&a...
